Project Design Prompt: AI Ecosystem RSS-Based Website Using GitHub Pages
üìå Project Title

Design and Develop a Static AI News & Insights Website Using GitHub Pages and RSS Feeds

üéØ Project Objective

Design, develop, and deploy a lightweight, responsive, and automated static website using GitHub Pages that aggregates and displays real-time content related to Artificial Intelligence tools, technologies, research, and global AI ecosystems through RSS feeds.

The platform will serve as a centralized hub for curated AI-related information, enabling users to stay updated with industry trends, innovations, and thought leadership without relying on algorithm-driven platforms.

üß© Problem Statement

With the rapid growth of AI tools, frameworks, startups, and research publications, relevant information is scattered across multiple platforms. Users lack a single, reliable, and transparent platform that delivers verified AI-related content without heavy personalization algorithms.

This project aims to solve this by building an RSS-powered aggregation website that presents structured, unbiased, and up-to-date AI content.

üõ†Ô∏è Scope of the Project

The website will:

Aggregate AI-related content from trusted RSS sources

Display categorized feeds (Tools, Research, Industry, Startups, Ethics, etc.)

Provide real-time updates on page load

Be hosted and maintained using GitHub Pages

Follow modern UI/UX standards

Support scalability for future features

